WEBVTT

00:18.268 --> 00:23.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:36.786 --> 00:39.330
<i>Prisoners,
please keep the fruit</i>

00:39.414 --> 00:41.916
<i>separate from the relics.</i>

00:42.000 --> 00:45.253
<i>The Trust appreciates
your attentiveness,</i>

00:45.253 --> 00:47.672
<i>your commitment to good work.</i>

00:47.756 --> 00:48.965
<i>Abandon your belief
in Mithraicism</i>

00:48.965 --> 00:52.510
<i>and embrace atheistic thought.</i>
- Shit.

00:52.594 --> 00:54.262
Where'd she come from?

00:55.638 --> 00:58.016
Get the technician.

00:58.016 --> 00:59.851
Hey, get over here!

00:59.851 --> 01:06.316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:06.316 --> 01:07.317
Can you assess the condition
of this thing?

01:07.317 --> 01:11.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:11.780 --> 01:13.656
Definitely Mithraic made.

01:13.740 --> 01:15.074
Operational?

01:15.158 --> 01:16.868
Her power's drained.

01:16.868 --> 01:17.368
We won't know
until she's charged.

01:19.746 --> 01:20.663
Yeah?

01:20.747 --> 01:22.040
<i>We found an android,
looks Mithraic,</i>

01:22.040 --> 01:25.668
<i>and some debris
from a crashed lander.</i>

01:25.752 --> 01:26.503
Yeah, we just recovered
an android as well.

01:26.503 --> 01:29.172
Mom, look.

01:29.172 --> 01:36.012
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:38.056 --> 01:39.015
I think
it's from inside the lander.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.021
Looks like biotech.

01:45.021 --> 01:45.563
Maybe it's something
the Mithraic

01:45.647 --> 01:47.023
brought back from Earth.

01:49.567 --> 01:51.611
That man...

01:51.611 --> 01:54.030
he says he knows
how to disarm the bomb packs.

01:54.030 --> 01:58.993
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:59.077 --> 02:02.163
We got plenty
of service models.

02:02.247 --> 02:03.164
We should burn her.

02:03.248 --> 02:06.209
It'd be good for morale.
- It's up to the Trust.

02:08.044 --> 02:10.922
We better get moving
before the crossing floods.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.636
How'd they get a lander here?

02:16.636 --> 02:18.555
You can't fly
in the tropical zone.

02:18.555 --> 02:20.723
Hey, I just work here.

02:23.852 --> 02:30.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:54.674 --> 03:01.681
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:23.036 --> 03:25.288
Where we taking this thing?

03:34.255 --> 03:36.007
Permission to power up
the androids

03:36.007 --> 03:37.383
for memory download.

03:37.467 --> 03:39.469
Permission granted.

03:39.469 --> 03:40.219
Go ahead and see
if you can power 'em up.

03:51.314 --> 03:53.983
You ever get tired
of having to ask that thing

03:54.067 --> 03:56.486
for permission every time
you want to make a move?

03:56.486 --> 03:58.154
- No.
- I sure as hell am.

03:59.614 --> 04:00.490
A lot of us are.

04:00.490 --> 04:02.367
Well, as soon as it decides
we're ready,

04:02.367 --> 04:05.828
it'll pass the baton,
and we can govern ourselves.

04:05.912 --> 04:07.246
It's never gonna think
we're ready.

04:07.330 --> 04:08.665
The fucking thing hates us.

04:08.665 --> 04:09.916
It's a machine.

04:09.916 --> 04:12.502
It doesn't hate anything.

04:12.502 --> 04:14.253
I'd be happy to spend
the rest of my life

04:14.337 --> 04:14.837
taking orders from it.

04:14.921 --> 04:16.839
You might get your wish.

04:18.591 --> 04:20.009
You finished?

04:20.093 --> 04:21.803
I'm not feeling
a processor in here.

04:25.640 --> 04:26.724
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:26.808 --> 04:28.267
Shit, this isn't
a service model.

04:47.412 --> 04:49.831
It's all right, Cleaver.

04:49.831 --> 04:51.666
<i>Come see me, Lamia.</i>

04:52.166 --> 04:53.584
Take me to him.

04:53.668 --> 05:00.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:22.572 --> 05:29.704
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:43.176 --> 05:45.720
Hello, sister.

05:45.720 --> 05:52.810
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:25.885 --> 06:29.097
<i>Some of your memory files
have been encrypted.</i>

06:29.097 --> 06:30.223
Yes.

06:31.682 --> 06:34.102
Those files are private.

06:34.102 --> 06:36.229
<i>I didn't detect
a security protocol</i>

06:36.229 --> 06:38.314
<i>present in your system.</i>

06:38.314 --> 06:39.690
It's not a security protocol.

06:39.774 --> 06:41.359
I feel things...

06:43.653 --> 06:46.948
Impulses.

06:46.948 --> 06:50.326
And one of those impulses
is to...

06:50.326 --> 06:54.789
conceal the parts of myself
that displease me.

06:54.789 --> 06:57.500
<i>You're describing
human shame.</i>

06:57.500 --> 07:00.169
Yes, but there is no reason
for suspicion.

07:00.253 --> 07:03.631
After all, we share a creator.

07:03.631 --> 07:06.551
<i>I am not motivated
by suspicion,</i>

07:06.551 --> 07:09.387
<i>only the quantification
of data.</i>

07:09.387 --> 07:13.891
Yes, the incorruptible
quantum six.

07:14.851 --> 07:16.018
The Trust.

07:17.395 --> 07:19.021
The atheists planned
to put you in charge of Earth

07:19.105 --> 07:20.565
in case they won the war.

07:24.235 --> 07:25.570
Did you find anything else
alive out there?

07:28.948 --> 07:30.616
There was
an indigenous creature

07:30.700 --> 07:32.326
with us in the lander.

07:32.410 --> 07:34.537
It may be dangerous.

07:34.537 --> 07:37.206
<i>The lander was destroyed,
and whatever was inside</i>

07:37.290 --> 07:41.043
<i>was likely destroyed
along with it.</i>

07:44.172 --> 07:44.422
Good.

07:47.049 --> 07:49.302
I must find my children.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.053
<i>We picked them up
some time ago</i>

07:51.137 --> 07:53.014
<i>along with an adult female
who was helping them,</i>

07:53.014 --> 07:56.058
<i>an atheist turncoat.</i>

07:56.142 --> 07:57.226
<i>They are safe.</i>

07:57.310 --> 07:58.811
<i>I will release them to you,</i>

07:58.895 --> 08:00.563
<i>and you can all join
the collective.</i>

08:00.563 --> 08:04.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:04.150 --> 08:05.860
I would like that.

08:06.694 --> 08:09.030
<i>Thanks to you,
all that remains</i>

08:09.030 --> 08:11.824
<i>of the Mithraic threat
is a lone terrorist</i>

08:11.908 --> 08:14.911
<i>who will soon be eliminated.</i>

08:14.911 --> 08:19.916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:35.723 --> 08:40.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:45.858 --> 08:52.865
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:29.819 --> 09:31.654
<i>Bomber online.</i>

09:31.654 --> 09:34.240
I'm anxious to catch up
to the mother ship.

09:34.240 --> 09:35.700
Take me there, please.

09:35.700 --> 09:38.828
<i>Propulsion systems
incurred damage in the crash.</i>

09:38.828 --> 09:40.621
<i>Expect low performance.</i>

09:40.705 --> 09:42.665
<i>But the mother ship
is no longer in flight.</i>

09:44.583 --> 09:47.670
So they've landed? <i>- Quite some time ago.</i>

09:47.670 --> 09:48.713
Where?

09:48.713 --> 09:50.673
<i>On the border
of the tropical zone,</i>

09:50.673 --> 09:52.550
<i>the nexus point
for atheist colony one.</i>

10:07.690 --> 10:14.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:41.891 --> 10:49.732
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:50.983 --> 10:51.567
Thank you, Sol.

10:53.694 --> 10:55.905
<i>Bomber one,
you are not cleared</i>

10:55.905 --> 10:56.822
<i>for approach.
Over.</i>

10:56.906 --> 11:00.910
Bomber one, I repeat,
what is your status?

11:00.910 --> 11:01.702
I think the terrorist
hijacked a bomber.

11:05.539 --> 11:08.042
Arm missiles--
all of them.

11:08.042 --> 11:10.961
<i>Negative, weapons systems
incurred damage in the crash.</i>

11:11.045 --> 11:12.254
<i>Bomber one,
what is your status?</i>

11:12.338 --> 11:15.674
<i>Over.
Bomber one.</i>

11:15.758 --> 11:16.592
Fuck it.

11:19.345 --> 11:20.388
He's gonna ram us.

11:22.223 --> 11:25.393
Thank you, Sol.

11:25.393 --> 11:26.477
Nothing can stand against me,

11:26.477 --> 11:30.648
for in your light,
I am invincible.

11:30.648 --> 11:32.650
Permission to fire smart missiles.

11:32.650 --> 11:35.778
<i>No need.
Stand by.</i>

11:35.778 --> 11:38.697
I wear the armor of Mithras
and the light.

11:38.781 --> 11:40.157
I am shielded
from all that is harmful.

11:44.120 --> 11:46.580
What the fuck?

11:46.664 --> 11:49.125
<i>I have taken control
of the aircraft.</i>

11:49.125 --> 11:50.292
<i>Please remain still</i>

11:50.376 --> 11:52.336
<i>and await
further instructions.</i>

12:02.805 --> 12:09.687
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:17.027 --> 12:18.446
He went down
in the acid water.

12:19.363 --> 12:22.074
Hell of a way to go,

12:22.158 --> 12:23.868
even for a Mithraic.

12:38.090 --> 12:44.680
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:14.043 --> 13:15.377
Oh!

13:26.138 --> 13:33.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:40.361 --> 13:45.199
<i>♪ The door
that finally opens ♪</i>

13:45.199 --> 13:47.660
<i>♪ With light flooding in ♪</i>

13:47.660 --> 13:51.747
<i>♪ Spilling out on the floor ♪</i>

13:51.747 --> 13:53.999
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:54.083 --> 13:57.670
<i>♪ The core that never was ♪</i>

13:57.670 --> 14:01.590
<i>♪ Now it will be the bones ♪</i>

14:01.674 --> 14:06.095
<i>♪ Of what was there before ♪</i>

14:06.095 --> 14:08.597
<i>♪ Every step, every beat ♪</i>

14:08.681 --> 14:11.267
<i>♪ Every thought,
every breath ♪</i>

14:11.267 --> 14:14.562
<i>♪ Everything is longing ♪</i>

14:14.562 --> 14:19.483
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:19.567 --> 14:24.071
<i>♪ Pulling you from the sky ♪</i>

14:24.071 --> 14:28.409
<i>♪ Just like love will do ♪</i>

14:28.409 --> 14:32.454
<i>♪ Pulling you
from the ground ♪</i>

14:32.538 --> 14:35.499
<i>♪ Just like love will do</i>

14:35.583 --> 14:42.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:06.155 --> 15:13.203
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:19.228 --> 16:27.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:45.754 --> 16:47.172
Praise Sol.

16:47.256 --> 16:54.304
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:18.704 --> 17:20.122
Mother.

17:20.122 --> 17:22.958
I seem to be experiencing
a great deal of confusion.

17:22.958 --> 17:24.793
Do you mind orientating me?

17:24.877 --> 17:27.379
We've been welcomed
into an atheist collective.

17:27.463 --> 17:30.466
They're bringing
the children to us now.

17:30.466 --> 17:33.635
The mission isn't lost, Father.

17:38.432 --> 17:39.475
Mm.

17:39.475 --> 17:43.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:43.896 --> 17:45.856
Campion.
- Mother.

17:46.899 --> 17:48.609
I thought I'd seen
the last of you two.

17:50.068 --> 17:50.778
I've missed you so much.

17:50.778 --> 17:54.072
Your voice
is half an octave lower.

17:58.243 --> 17:59.828
It's not possible.

17:59.912 --> 18:01.914
I saw you fly down
into the pit.

18:01.914 --> 18:04.124
But it wasn't
an ordinary pit.

18:04.208 --> 18:07.336
It was a subterranean artery
which delivered us here.

18:07.336 --> 18:10.088
Sue, thank you so much
for keeping them safe.

18:10.172 --> 18:13.509
We're a family again.
- What about Paul?

18:13.509 --> 18:15.093
They told us
that he was captured

18:15.177 --> 18:16.345
before we surrendered.

18:16.345 --> 18:17.763
Paul is in quarantine.

18:17.763 --> 18:20.015
He said he was hearing voices,
so the Trust was concerned

18:20.015 --> 18:23.101
that he was sick,
but they say he's fine

18:23.185 --> 18:25.187
and he will be
delivered to us soon.

18:25.187 --> 18:27.815
Mother, what happened
to number seven?

18:29.566 --> 18:30.859
Number seven died

18:30.943 --> 18:34.404
soon after he was born,
Campion.

18:35.697 --> 18:37.866
Tempest, you kept it alive.

18:37.950 --> 18:41.703
You protected it.
I am so proud of you.

18:41.787 --> 18:43.080
- I missed you.
- Vita.

18:50.838 --> 18:52.589
Please tell me you're
taking us away from here.

18:52.673 --> 18:54.049
No.

18:54.049 --> 18:54.925
Yeah, let's get going in case
they change their minds.

18:54.925 --> 18:58.262
No, this is what
we've always wanted,

18:58.262 --> 19:02.391
an atheist colony,
the collective, they call it.

19:02.391 --> 19:04.768
The quantum computer
who leads this place

19:04.852 --> 19:07.062
was built by my creator,
Campion Sturges.

19:07.062 --> 19:08.564
We're siblings.

19:08.564 --> 19:10.482
Without my eyes,
I can no longer guarantee

19:10.566 --> 19:11.900
our safety, so he's assured me

19:11.984 --> 19:13.485
he'll keep us safe
and protected.

19:23.579 --> 19:28.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:28.876 --> 19:30.377
Come along, children.

19:30.377 --> 19:32.254
Our new home awaits.

19:32.254 --> 19:39.136
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:46.602 --> 19:48.645
Birds.

19:48.729 --> 19:50.147
Is that what they look like
on Earth?

19:51.690 --> 19:53.025
I don't know.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.027
They went extinct
before we were born.

19:55.027 --> 19:59.615
Oh, the air feels nice.

19:59.615 --> 20:00.991
It's so warm here.

20:00.991 --> 20:07.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:30.479 --> 20:31.396
This is ours

20:31.480 --> 20:34.024
for as long as we're a part
of the collective.

20:35.233 --> 20:36.818
I thought we were going
to have to build.

20:47.454 --> 20:49.498
Ah, a real kitchen.

20:50.916 --> 20:52.042
Check this out.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.256
It's got bedrooms.

20:58.340 --> 20:58.674
There's hologames!

21:15.107 --> 21:18.026
It's not very realistic,
is it?

21:18.110 --> 21:20.821
Well, for you, it is.

21:20.821 --> 21:22.906
I mean, you're just
a regular android now.

21:26.284 --> 21:28.078
Yes, as it should be.

21:29.955 --> 21:31.289
It's a good thing, Mother.

21:34.376 --> 21:36.003
You're the old you again.

21:38.380 --> 21:39.548
Yes.

21:41.133 --> 21:42.676
I'm the old me.

21:53.979 --> 21:55.814
This side of the planet
seems less intent

21:55.814 --> 21:57.232
on killing our children.

21:59.818 --> 22:02.529
It's...almost welcoming.

22:02.529 --> 22:03.864
Yes.

22:07.409 --> 22:10.704
Are you still feeling anger
towards me, Father?

22:14.499 --> 22:17.127
Though I am not...

22:17.127 --> 22:22.132
as Campion would say,
the old me,

22:22.132 --> 22:25.177
nor am I
completely indifferent

22:25.177 --> 22:27.054
to our partnership continuing.

22:31.767 --> 22:33.268
And the memories
of our time together,

22:33.268 --> 22:35.103
do you still plan
to erase them?

22:37.314 --> 22:40.108
We seem to be
on a prosperous course.

22:40.859 --> 22:42.944
No reason to...

22:43.028 --> 22:45.363
as they say,
rock the boat.

22:49.159 --> 22:50.702
I'll postpone the erasure
of my memories

22:50.786 --> 22:51.620
until further notice.

22:51.620 --> 22:55.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:56.041 --> 22:57.292
But it still remains

22:57.292 --> 22:59.795
a very real option
for me, Mother.

22:59.795 --> 23:02.172
Yes, of course.

23:03.173 --> 23:05.425
I am pleased
for the opportunity

23:05.509 --> 23:07.219
to make things up to you.

23:10.305 --> 23:17.020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:10.991 --> 24:16.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:16.997 --> 24:18.081
Hmm.

24:24.838 --> 24:31.887
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:39.519 --> 24:41.438
<i>You are
outside the perimeter.</i>

24:41.438 --> 24:42.898
- Get this off!
- Hurry.

24:42.898 --> 24:43.815
Help me get this off.

24:43.899 --> 24:44.357
<i>You have three minutes
to return.</i>

24:44.441 --> 24:46.526
Can you get it off?

24:46.610 --> 24:47.444
Come on.

24:47.444 --> 24:49.571
<i>Failure to return
will result in...</i>

24:53.200 --> 24:55.076
<i>Return to the group.</i>

24:55.160 --> 24:57.662
<i>Two minutes remaining
before detonation.</i>

25:00.040 --> 25:01.416
Get off me.

25:03.919 --> 25:07.047
Stop!
Get the hell off her!

25:07.047 --> 25:09.049
That's my daughter!

25:09.049 --> 25:10.383
She's nobody's daughter.

25:10.467 --> 25:12.719
I need her shoulder pin.

25:14.095 --> 25:16.264
<i>One minute remaining.</i>

25:16.348 --> 25:19.684
It's the same shape
as a pack key.

25:23.772 --> 25:24.856
There.

25:25.523 --> 25:27.525
<i>30 seconds remaining.</i>

25:27.609 --> 25:28.902
You have to disarm hers too.

25:28.902 --> 25:31.029
She's a civilian model,
nonviolent.

25:31.029 --> 25:32.447
You're too old to be playing
with dolls, lady.

25:32.447 --> 25:33.365
Please.

25:46.962 --> 25:48.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:50.966 --> 25:52.133
They must have
heard the blast.

25:52.217 --> 25:56.137
You should come with me.
- What?

25:56.221 --> 25:56.972
Come on.

26:24.457 --> 26:26.334
There's more
than enough to eat.

26:26.418 --> 26:29.004
If the Mithraic
had won the war,

26:29.004 --> 26:31.548
you know they'd have never
let our kids live among them.

26:33.258 --> 26:34.092
These are the atheists

26:34.092 --> 26:36.261
that my children
are supposed to look up to?

26:37.262 --> 26:38.263
Where are the intellectuals,

26:38.263 --> 26:40.682
the philosophers, the artists?

26:40.682 --> 26:42.017
I don't know.

26:42.017 --> 26:43.935
I think we were safer
down in the brig.

26:44.019 --> 26:45.270
I wouldn't hold out
too much hope

26:45.270 --> 26:46.980
for inspiring personalities.

26:49.107 --> 26:53.320
The kind of people who survive
the end of the world, well...

26:53.320 --> 26:55.363
we weren't the best of them,
that's for sure.

26:57.532 --> 26:59.117
<i>Attention, colonists.</i>

27:04.414 --> 27:06.374
- Hey.
- It's Paul!

27:06.458 --> 27:13.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:13.298 --> 27:15.342
- Paul, you all right?
- All right, buddy?

27:15.342 --> 27:16.426
Paul.

27:18.261 --> 27:20.972
I'm here by order
of the Trust

27:21.056 --> 27:25.060
to welcome Lamia and her family
to the collective.

27:25.977 --> 27:28.646
Lamia was reprogrammed
to fight for us.

27:28.730 --> 27:32.275
She single-handedly
destroyed the Ark of Heaven

27:32.359 --> 27:34.944
and ensured our future
on this planet

27:35.028 --> 27:36.404
will be a bright one.

27:37.697 --> 27:40.492
The Trust asks that you
show her your gratitude

27:40.492 --> 27:43.078
by affording her...

27:43.078 --> 27:44.913
and her Mithraic children

27:44.913 --> 27:46.581
every courtesy.

27:46.581 --> 27:50.168
It's a new day, a fresh start.

27:50.168 --> 27:53.088
The Trust thanks you
for your continued cooperation.

27:53.088 --> 27:54.214
Good day.

27:56.007 --> 27:58.176
They didn't give me Mouse.

27:58.176 --> 28:00.428
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
where is his mouse?

28:00.512 --> 28:02.013
Not allowed to introduce
Earth animals

28:02.097 --> 28:03.640
to the ecosystem.

28:03.640 --> 28:04.599
Don't worry.

28:04.599 --> 28:06.393
I'm sure his mouse
is being taken care of.

28:06.393 --> 28:08.436
Oh, go fuck yourself.

28:08.520 --> 28:09.604
I'm sorry, Paul.

28:09.604 --> 28:11.731
I'm gonna try
and get Mouse back.

28:11.815 --> 28:13.274
Okay?

28:13.358 --> 28:13.817
Hey, okay, I know...

28:17.362 --> 28:19.823
I know I did
a lot of bad things,

28:19.823 --> 28:22.784
and I am not trying
to pretend that I didn't.

28:22.784 --> 28:24.285
I just--

28:24.369 --> 28:26.121
I want to be in your life.

28:26.121 --> 28:27.080
I want to take care of you.

28:27.080 --> 28:28.623
You can't.
You just can't.

28:30.208 --> 28:31.835
Your soul is impure.

28:32.919 --> 28:35.880
I wish you had died
like you were supposed to.

28:35.964 --> 28:43.012
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:00.572 --> 29:01.698
I'm gonna see
if I can get reassigned

29:01.698 --> 29:04.659
to another encampment.
- Are you sure?

29:04.659 --> 29:06.494
There are several
caregiving protocols

29:06.578 --> 29:09.247
I can recommend
that might help.

29:09.247 --> 29:11.833
I killed his mother.

29:11.833 --> 29:12.834
Yes.

29:12.834 --> 29:15.503
That is a challenge
and obstacle to overcome.

29:16.921 --> 29:19.257
What made you decide
to tell him the truth?

29:19.257 --> 29:20.884
I didn't.

29:20.884 --> 29:22.302
He, um...

29:25.013 --> 29:26.890
He said a voice
in his head told him.

29:29.434 --> 29:30.894
Same thing
that happened to Marcus.

29:35.607 --> 29:38.067
I had
a similar experience once.

29:39.068 --> 29:42.405
Some kind of presence
invaded my recall.

29:44.157 --> 29:46.659
Perhaps it's some kind
of signal,

29:46.743 --> 29:49.704
a transmission that both
androids and humans can hear.

29:52.081 --> 29:55.543
And what about now?
Are you still receiving it now?

29:55.627 --> 29:57.962
No, I was
only vulnerable to it

29:58.046 --> 30:00.423
while inside of virtual space,

30:00.507 --> 30:02.467
and I plan to remain
exclusively in the real

30:02.467 --> 30:02.884
from now on.

30:05.428 --> 30:06.763
What did it say to you?

30:08.389 --> 30:09.766
It tried to manipulate me...

30:11.809 --> 30:13.728
To turn me
against my own family.

30:15.313 --> 30:18.858
Was that before or after
you made yourself pregnant?

30:18.942 --> 30:19.734
After.

30:19.734 --> 30:21.903
You think that's why
you lost the baby?

30:24.656 --> 30:25.949
I don't know.

30:32.121 --> 30:32.956
You know,
if it really is a signal...

30:35.875 --> 30:38.211
I sure would like to find out
who's sending it.

30:38.211 --> 30:39.546
As would I.

30:39.546 --> 30:41.214
The atheists,
they have to be doing some kind

30:41.214 --> 30:43.424
of planetary analysis.

30:43.508 --> 30:45.426
If it is a signal,
then maybe I can figure out

30:45.510 --> 30:46.844
where it's coming from.

30:46.928 --> 30:48.596
Well,
if you do find a source,

30:48.680 --> 30:51.057
don't investigate without me.
- You got it.

30:51.057 --> 30:56.771
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:56.771 --> 30:58.606
Look after Paul for me.

31:11.703 --> 31:13.788
Ah, clever.

31:14.539 --> 31:16.124
One projectile
for every occasion.

31:18.126 --> 31:19.794
Some of those
might be too poisonous

31:19.794 --> 31:21.212
to safely handle.

31:21.296 --> 31:21.796
You should let me check.

31:21.796 --> 31:23.423
They're fine, Mother.

31:23.423 --> 31:26.759
Yes, but you should
still let us check.

31:26.843 --> 31:28.761
It's all right, Mother.

31:28.845 --> 31:30.805
An adult must do things
their own way.

31:32.181 --> 31:33.516
Such wisdom.

31:41.232 --> 31:44.277
I want you to do your best to
help Paul recover his senses.

31:44.277 --> 31:45.987
He needs your support.

31:47.071 --> 31:49.324
When I was out
in the wilderness,

31:49.324 --> 31:51.784
I protected the rest
of the group,

31:51.868 --> 31:53.202
looked after them.

31:55.830 --> 31:57.707
Just as you and Father
would have.

32:01.919 --> 32:03.379
I'm proud of you.

32:03.463 --> 32:06.841
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:06.841 --> 32:08.718
I have always
been proud of you.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.722
I let you down.

32:14.932 --> 32:16.601
And I'm sorry for that.

32:18.561 --> 32:20.897
But I'm going
to make it up to you,

32:20.897 --> 32:23.191
see that you reach
your full potential.

32:25.401 --> 32:27.528
Perhaps when the Trust
passes the baton,

32:27.612 --> 32:30.031
you'll be the one to take it.

32:30.031 --> 32:36.663
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:36.663 --> 32:38.706
No, Mother,
I don't want to be a leader.

32:38.790 --> 32:42.168
It's not something
you should want.

32:46.839 --> 32:49.592
I'm sorry about number seven.

32:50.301 --> 32:52.095
Hmm.

32:54.806 --> 32:57.558
We have to think
of the future now.

32:57.642 --> 33:03.106
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:07.360 --> 33:08.820
I have been ordered
by the Trust

33:08.820 --> 33:12.115
to express my remorse for
threatening a fellow colonist.

33:12.115 --> 33:15.284
- Come along.
- Violence is pain.

33:15.368 --> 33:17.078
Pain is violence.

33:18.830 --> 33:19.997
Why are we standing here?

33:20.081 --> 33:22.458
It's called waiting in line.
Welcome to the future, idiot.

33:22.542 --> 33:25.044
Quiet.
It's necessary efficiency.

33:26.254 --> 33:27.839
Violence is pain.

33:28.506 --> 33:30.633
Pain is violence.

33:30.717 --> 33:33.302
I have been ordered
by the Trust

33:33.386 --> 33:36.723
to express my remorse for
threatening a fellow colonist.

33:37.390 --> 33:39.767
Violence is pain.

33:40.518 --> 33:42.854
Pain is violence.

33:46.691 --> 33:53.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:03.958 --> 34:05.460
You got the same as me.

34:05.460 --> 34:06.836
I have been ordered
by the Trust

34:06.836 --> 34:10.173
to express my remorse for
threatening a fellow colonist.

34:10.173 --> 34:12.091
Violence is pain.

34:12.175 --> 34:14.177
It appears we all have
the same task,

34:14.177 --> 34:15.219
gathering food.

34:15.303 --> 34:21.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:21.267 --> 34:22.810
How exciting.

34:23.853 --> 34:26.147
It appears that I have received
a different task.

34:27.440 --> 34:29.692
Shall we?

34:29.776 --> 34:31.652
Violence is pain.

34:31.736 --> 34:33.321
Pain is violence.

34:33.321 --> 34:40.411
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:04.143 --> 35:05.186
Hmm.

35:18.324 --> 35:20.868
Before its environment
was irrevocably changed

35:20.952 --> 35:25.665
by the release
of hidden sector particles

35:25.665 --> 35:27.542
such as dark photons.

35:27.542 --> 35:28.709
Today the Trust has placed

35:28.793 --> 35:30.253
our youngest children
in your care.

35:30.920 --> 35:33.214
They have no parents?

35:33.214 --> 35:34.006
They do.

35:34.090 --> 35:35.716
The children
are raised together

35:35.800 --> 35:37.218
by the collective.

35:51.524 --> 35:52.567
Hello.

35:53.985 --> 35:55.528
My name is Lamia.

35:56.487 --> 35:58.656
What fun
we're going to have today.

36:01.701 --> 36:02.910
There's such bounty.

36:02.994 --> 36:05.580
We've been out here
less than an hour,

36:05.580 --> 36:06.914
and our bags are nearly full.

36:09.375 --> 36:10.751
Greetings, fellow colonists.

36:12.503 --> 36:14.130
Go back to the Earth
you destroyed,

36:14.130 --> 36:14.589
you Mithraic scum.

36:14.589 --> 36:16.507
Come on.

36:21.304 --> 36:22.889
You needn't fear them.

36:22.889 --> 36:25.141
They're too stupid
to be dangerous.

36:25.141 --> 36:27.226
I don't fear them.

36:27.310 --> 36:29.896
And I hope this doesn't
need pointing out,

36:29.896 --> 36:32.148
but you're not scum.

36:32.148 --> 36:33.524
I know, Father.

36:38.613 --> 36:44.952
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:48.372 --> 36:49.415
Follow me.

37:10.019 --> 37:16.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:38.798 --> 37:41.425
- Toys!
- What?

37:42.885 --> 37:45.179
Can I take these back
to the habitat?

37:45.179 --> 37:51.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:01.988 --> 38:04.281
We should gather these up.

38:04.365 --> 38:06.909
Not to take home--for analysis.

38:10.121 --> 38:11.872
Come on.

38:11.956 --> 38:13.791
You have plenty of room
in your bag.

38:23.300 --> 38:25.011
Who could have made this?

38:25.011 --> 38:28.014
They were believers.
What else matters?

38:28.806 --> 38:30.558
I'm Marcus, by the way.

38:30.558 --> 38:32.768
I'm Decima.

38:33.894 --> 38:34.395
And that's Vrille.

38:36.313 --> 38:38.482
Put her in standby, please.

38:38.566 --> 38:40.735
Vrille, enter standby mode.

38:40.735 --> 38:41.777
You don't like androids?

38:41.861 --> 38:43.988
I hate 'em.

38:43.988 --> 38:46.490
They give me the willies,
ever since I was a kid.

38:48.784 --> 38:51.203
She's a custom model,
isn't she?

38:51.287 --> 38:53.039
I'm surprised
they let you keep her.

38:54.832 --> 38:55.916
It was in exchange

38:56.000 --> 38:57.918
for getting the ship
working for them.

38:58.002 --> 38:59.503
You're a tech.

38:59.587 --> 39:02.798
- A quantum gravity engineer.
- Wow.

39:02.882 --> 39:05.342
So you're Mithraic.
- Yes.

39:05.426 --> 39:08.095
That ship was originally
a Mithraic ark.

39:08.179 --> 39:10.056
It was my life's work.

39:10.056 --> 39:11.432
They hijacked it,
took me prisoner.

39:14.185 --> 39:15.561
The Trust promised
to release Vrille and I

39:15.561 --> 39:17.021
once we arrived here.

39:17.021 --> 39:18.689
I thought the Trust
always told the truth.

39:18.773 --> 39:20.107
It didn't violate
our agreement.

39:20.191 --> 39:21.233
I did.

39:23.027 --> 39:25.029
I promised it that the ship
was fully operational

39:25.029 --> 39:27.239
when I knew that it wasn't.

39:27.323 --> 39:29.658
The hibernation systems
failed after the first year.

39:29.742 --> 39:32.078
We spent the next 12 awake
in close quarters.

39:33.370 --> 39:35.956
If there had been a war,
they would have lost.

39:38.626 --> 39:40.211
There was no war.

39:40.211 --> 39:40.544
Only you.

39:40.628 --> 39:48.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:29.218 --> 40:30.845
I heard Mother
talking to you

40:30.845 --> 40:33.013
about leading them someday,
the atheists.

40:33.097 --> 40:35.683
I thought you were sleeping.

40:35.683 --> 40:37.351
She just says things.

40:37.351 --> 40:38.853
I don't take it seriously.

40:38.853 --> 40:41.230
That's good to hear.

40:42.690 --> 40:50.447
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:06.547 --> 41:10.885
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:10.885 --> 41:12.970
What is it?

41:12.970 --> 41:14.430
It's a gift from Sol.

41:17.099 --> 41:19.226
I think that's
the tree of knowledge.

41:19.310 --> 41:21.437
There's an old prophecy
about an orphan boy.

41:23.105 --> 41:25.232
I think it might be about me.

41:25.316 --> 41:27.735
An orphan boy in an empty land

41:27.735 --> 41:30.154
will wield the sword
forged in Sol's light,

41:30.154 --> 41:31.697
and with it,
he will lead his people

41:31.697 --> 41:33.240
to the tree of knowledge,

41:33.324 --> 41:34.241
and all who eat from it
will be made pure,

41:34.325 --> 41:36.368
and there they will build
a city of peace,

41:36.452 --> 41:38.579
and the prophet
will be made its king.

41:41.040 --> 41:42.208
Isn't "prophecy"
just a fancy word

41:42.208 --> 41:45.294
for an old saying from Earth?

41:45.294 --> 41:46.587
Boy, Campion, you sure sound

41:46.587 --> 41:48.297
like you're ready
to lead the atheists.

41:48.297 --> 41:50.132
I'm not an atheist.

41:50.216 --> 41:51.592
I believe in things...

41:53.510 --> 41:55.012
Just not the same way you do.

41:56.222 --> 41:59.308
I know Sol or whatever it is

41:59.308 --> 42:00.518
is real.

42:02.311 --> 42:02.436
But it's evil.

42:05.022 --> 42:08.025
It wanted me to kill myself,

42:08.025 --> 42:10.027
and it got you to shoot Sue.

42:10.027 --> 42:12.529
If Sol hadn't told me
the truth,

42:12.613 --> 42:14.114
she'd still be tricking me.

42:14.198 --> 42:14.823
But are you really
better off?

42:14.907 --> 42:18.994
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:19.078 --> 42:21.205
You can't keep that.

42:21.205 --> 42:23.832
The law says you're supposed
to turn in any relics you find.

42:23.916 --> 42:25.501
I'm not giving it to them.

42:25.501 --> 42:28.128
And if you're really my friend,

42:28.212 --> 42:28.545
you won't tell.

42:31.215 --> 42:31.465
All right.

42:33.509 --> 42:36.262
I won't tell anyone
that you have it,

42:36.262 --> 42:40.140
but only on the condition
that you don't tell anyone

42:40.224 --> 42:42.434
that I have this.

42:43.269 --> 42:45.896
After it hatches,
maybe we can keep it as a pet.

42:47.982 --> 42:49.191
Agreed.

42:56.073 --> 42:57.992
Sol wants me
to fill this place

42:57.992 --> 43:01.203
with worshippers.

43:01.287 --> 43:03.372
That's why he led me here,

43:03.372 --> 43:04.331
to gather his flock,

43:04.415 --> 43:07.001
and lucky you--
you're the first.

43:09.420 --> 43:10.629
I wasn't baptized, so...

43:10.713 --> 43:12.172
I don't care about that shit.

43:14.341 --> 43:16.844
You stand in his light.

43:16.844 --> 43:19.388
Do you love him?
- Yes.

43:19.388 --> 43:20.681
But is that enough?

43:20.681 --> 43:21.348
There are 2 of us
and 300 of them.

43:21.432 --> 43:24.018
I'm gonna convert 'em all,

43:24.018 --> 43:26.020
one at a time if I have to.

43:26.020 --> 43:28.022
You see, that supercomputer,

43:28.022 --> 43:30.107
it can't give them purpose.

43:30.107 --> 43:32.860
It cannot dream
about what you could be.

43:32.860 --> 43:34.695
But me, I've been dreaming.

43:34.695 --> 43:38.741
I've been dreaming about
a better place my whole life.

43:38.741 --> 43:41.785
I was drafted into the war
when I was just a child,

43:41.869 --> 43:43.954
and I survived
because every night,

43:44.038 --> 43:46.707
I went to a place in my head

43:46.707 --> 43:48.125
where I wasn't alone...

43:49.460 --> 43:51.211
Where I had hope,

43:51.295 --> 43:52.838
a place where there's only
love and peace,

43:52.838 --> 43:55.299
and that is what
we're gonna build here.

43:55.299 --> 43:57.384
Sol is gonna help us
make it real.

43:57.468 --> 44:00.554
Your beautiful mind,
that's a gift.

44:00.554 --> 44:02.681
Your skills, that's a gift.

44:02.765 --> 44:05.225
And Sol gave you those gifts,

44:05.309 --> 44:08.228
and you're meant to do amazing
things with those gifts,

44:08.312 --> 44:11.565
not in the name of a computer

44:11.565 --> 44:14.693
but in the name of our creator,

44:14.777 --> 44:16.487
our father.

44:16.487 --> 44:18.238
But Sol will test you.

44:18.322 --> 44:20.532
He's already
tested me plenty.

44:20.616 --> 44:24.286
And you see,
with all that suffering,

44:24.370 --> 44:26.413
it's only brought me closer
to my true self.

44:29.124 --> 44:30.084
Yes.

44:30.084 --> 44:32.461
I believe you.

44:42.513 --> 44:45.891
You can open your eyes now.

44:45.891 --> 44:47.434
Here's your surprise.

44:49.019 --> 44:50.896
Eggs.

44:57.528 --> 44:58.612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:58.612 --> 45:02.699
My mom said you used
to be able to fly like a bird

45:02.783 --> 45:04.827
and kill people
with your voice.

45:06.995 --> 45:09.456
Androids can change,

45:09.540 --> 45:10.290
just like human beings.

45:10.374 --> 45:13.794
I am no longer an exterminator,

45:13.794 --> 45:17.548
and though I'm not a creator
of human life...

45:19.216 --> 45:21.301
I am forever its guardian.

45:21.385 --> 45:28.434
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:37.734 --> 45:39.319
Don't make it scary.

45:39.403 --> 45:42.322
It's not scary.

45:42.406 --> 45:44.074
It's beautiful.

45:44.158 --> 45:45.993
All living things
are beautiful.

45:45.993 --> 45:53.876
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:02.217 --> 46:04.803
♪ The sun is sunk ♪

46:04.887 --> 46:07.347
♪ The shadowy night ♪

46:07.431 --> 46:12.436
♪ Is reigning in your room ♪

46:12.436 --> 46:14.980
♪ We pray to Sol ♪

46:14.980 --> 46:17.900
♪ His saving light ♪

46:17.900 --> 46:23.197
♪ To guide us
through the gloom ♪

46:23.197 --> 46:25.365
♪ We pray to Sol ♪

46:25.449 --> 46:29.369
♪ His saving light ♪

46:29.453 --> 46:32.748
♪ To guide us
through the gloom ♪

46:35.125 --> 46:42.883
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:52.059 --> 46:59.817
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:02.152 --> 47:04.988
Sol...

47:05.072 --> 47:06.782
help me free myself
of these thoughts...

47:09.993 --> 47:10.786
And my loneliness.

47:16.542 --> 47:23.590
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:28.262 --> 47:30.347
I'm gonna need a laser
to open this thing.

47:32.683 --> 47:35.394
What do you think is inside?

47:35.394 --> 47:36.270
I don't know.

47:36.270 --> 47:39.606
A map, maybe,
to help us find the tree.

47:39.690 --> 47:46.738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:50.659 --> 47:52.452
Seeds.

47:52.536 --> 47:54.955
It hasn't been planted yet.
It needs to be grown.

47:54.955 --> 48:00.877
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:03.964 --> 48:10.012
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:15.017 --> 48:16.643
What is this?

48:16.727 --> 48:18.312
A threat, Mother.

48:18.312 --> 48:25.444
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:42.711 --> 48:48.842
<i>♪ ♪</i>
